.TH "lpfc_els_handle_rscn" 9 "lpfc_els_handle_rscn" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
lpfc_els_handle_rscn \- Handle rscn for a vport
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" lpfc_els_handle_rscn
.BI "(struct lpfc_vport *vport "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "vport" 12
pointer to a host virtual N_Port data structure.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine handles the Registration State Configuration Notification
(RSCN) for a \fIvport\fP. If login to NameServer does not exist, a new ndlp shall
be created and a Port Login (PLOGI) to the NameServer is issued. Otherwise,
if the ndlp to NameServer exists, a Common Transport (CT) command to the
NameServer shall be issued. If CT command to the NameServer fails to be
issued, the \fBlpfc_els_flush_rscn\fP routine shall be invoked to clean up any
RSCN activities with the \fIvport\fP.

Return code
0 - Cleaned up rscn on the \fIvport\fP
1 - Wait for plogi to name server before proceed
